\section{Conclusions and future work}
\label{sec:conclusion}

In this paper, we focused on the $W_{-1}$ branch of the Lambert $W$ function and we derived tractable closed-form upper and lower bounds. We then considered a network of two users and an access point, and we demonstrated that our proposed bounds can identify operational regions of mutually beneficial cooperation based on system characteristics, such as the channel quality and the employed transmission scheme. The derived expressions can be used to make decisions on whether nodes should cooperate or not, if their objective is to improve outage probability.

To illustrate the application of the Lambert function and the proposed bounds, we assumed that inter-user channels are perfect and uplink channels are statistically similar. Follow-on work will aim to derive conditions for cooperation in networks where inter-user channels can be reciprocal or independent and uplink channels can be statistically similar or dissimilar.








